<Content>, Nice Getaway This is a modest, but pleasant hotel. I have a slight disability (walk with a cane) and I found it easy to get around and the staff helpful and friendly. The beach is feet from our door (room #212..king size bed with sink and refrigerator). If you are looking for night life, excitement etc this is not the place for you...as others have said stay in San Juan. But, if you want to experience real Puerto Rico, you might want to start here. Route 3 does go right by the hotel...there is nothing to do about it...but within a few minutes we found some peaceful almost deserted beautiful beaches. Also, one can drive into the mountains north of Patillas for a day. We found ourselves staying close to the hotel for reading and swimming most days.Someone commented that the hotel's food was mediocre. We disagree. We had the best red snapper (Chillo) here and the mofungo was also very good. There are a couple of other options within a 15 minute ride for dinner, but the hotel food was just as good as we found locally. 
