<Content>Location Versus Faciliies My wife and I spent a night at this resort on 19 November 2007. We arrived after driving from the west side of Puerto Rico and lookign to explore the south east coast of the island. Although we arrived after 2:00 pm, our room was not ready. We waited at the bar and ordered from their menu. I recommend you eat at a local restaurant and save yourself the disappointment. We were given room 3 in building 3. The room was spacious, but the furtniture was a bit worn and the A/C unit did not work properly and left the floor wet immediately in front of it. Also, some of the windows by the room door were broken and could be open from the outside. I noticed this problem with most of the rooms in our building. The room had a small fridge and a kitchenette, but the A/C unit was over this area and anything left over the counter would become wet. There is no phone in the rooms, and I could not find one once the office closed for the night. Like most of the rooms in the facility, ours faced the beach. The water was only about 20 feet from our room. There are plenty of beach chairs and hammocks to lay around in the sun. I did not use the pool, but the place has a nice one with an area for kids. Overall the resort is in a great location and makes it easy to explore the coast, but at $117.00 a night we found it way over priced for the overal state of the facility. 
