<Content>No crowds, I liked this place alot! I stayed for TWO WEEKS with a group of people and we loved it. I agree -- it is noisy from road traffic at night because of the way the place sits on a bit of land between the road and the beach. Some nights worse than others. You just need to drink a few more Tequilla sunrises before you turn in for the night! 'Frige in the room, stock up whatever you like. The rooms all open to the quiet beachfront. Wake up in the morning, hear the water, open the door and there is your hammock. ten steps to breakfast out on the deck , hot coffee is waiting, sweet ladies bring you your meals outdoors. Don't be afraid to venture out down the road for dinner. All of us had dinners at several of the local restaurants up  down the road and they serve fresh fish, chicken and local fare. You can walk on the sand in flip flops to the little open air place 100 yards down and it was fine. Nothing to be afraid of. We walked home in the dark, no problems. The management was great and can give information about the local restaurants, it does seem like everything closed on Sundays, and some on Mondays. They celebrate lots of holidays so it's hard to predict the closings. Little bakery down the road was good, pastries, flan, a hot lunch can be had there too. Many of the lovely old houses up and down the road are being renovated and this area is up and coming hot property, I can see the future. Just don't expect luxury rooms here, this is water, sun and no crowds. I brought my paint box and sketch pad and it was me and the iguanas. 
