<Content>A Beautiful Place for Real Travelers I can't believe all of the so-so reviews I've read about the Caribe Playa! My husband and I love this place and would stay there again and again. If you don't know much about Puerto Rico and/ or are a vacation snob, maybe you should stay around touristy San Juan or spend $600 a night at the Horned Dorset, but if you are a real traveler who doesn't mind a basic room in exchange for beautiful views and a gorgeous location, this could be a good place for you. Yes, the beach is rocky, as are most beaches in southern PR, but still very pretty. Wear water shoes. This isn't Luquillo. But there are plenty of things that make up for it. Dinners were delicious, the pool was always clean, and we didn't have any mildew in our room! And please don't expect things to be like America; PR might be a U.S. possession, but it definitely has its own culture and way of doing things. If you want a vacation that is packaged perfection, go to an all-inclusive instead and let others enjoy undeveloped, undiscovered Patillas. 
