<Content>Romantic weekend with inconvenience We stayed at Caribe Playa Beach Resort in June of 2006. The view of this place is totally AMAZING! The pictures on the internet from the beach are exactly how it is, even better. However, the service and the place are something different. We believe that the rooms are outdated, and are overpriced. It's more like a family camp site where you pay $50.00/day than a hotel. Even more, we wouldn't call it a hotel, is more like a Motel. The staff of the motel do not have any training in customer service. They really don't care if you are satisfied or not. The beaches are just for you to enjoy it with your eyes. They are rocky and dangerous beaches. We had to go to another beach 15 min away from the place and pay to use it. The parking space is very, very limited and sometimes you have to park on the road and if you get lucky to find a space it could get blocked by other cars. As a result of this, you will have to wait for the motel staff to call every room to have them take out the cars. To eat at the hotel you have to make reservations an hour before they start serving and you have to pick between two dishes. The food is not good at all. For tourists, is really a bad representation of our cuisine. When we received our dinner the meat was completely raw and they had to cook it again.Overall, we had a good time not because the motel and the staff did something to make our stay better, but because we tried not to think in all the inconvenients that we had. If we are in the area again some other time, we would not stay in this place and definetely not recommend it to anyone. Maybe just to drive by and take pictures of the beach. 
