<Content>Room liveable, management should be shot twice and then shot again Recenlty purchased by a local rich guy that lives in San Juan, he let his son run the hotel. Juvenile, immature and unable to handle the simplest problems. Fortunately, an older more mature manager had just been recently hired to give the kid some lessons. All I can say is THANK GOD!The hotel has 3 units, one which had no running hot water. I watched for hours while waiting for cheeseburger has one after another customer came to complain about the hot water situation. The young lady who was in charge had no idea what that meant and certainly could not handle the unhappy group. She finally refused to answer questions or call anyone to take care of the water heater. About 90 minutes into my hamburger order, a young man, the manager showed up for about 5 minutes, listened to some complaints, got his dinner and left. That was the first and last of him. Another 90 minutes later, I got my hamburger. I was the first to order and the very last to eat. Good burger though.The rooms are nothing special. You have no choice but to use the AC because the windows have plastic covering them. Only the bathroom let in outside air. Phones? Well, maybe, maybe not.The saving grace was the older gentlemen that we met the next morning. Professional, courteous, and MATURE. It was a travesty when we found out that many of the people could have been moved to other units, but the young lady and her boss seemed totally indifferent about it.If the girl and kid are gone, this might be a decent place to stay. 
