<Content>Just OK I booked 9 nights at this place via a travel site on the internet- with no refunds after I checked in- big mistake! The place is ok, don't get me wrong. The views are breath taking, and the grounds are tastfully decorated. The staff here is wonderful, and I give them an A+ in service. The food at the restaurant is good, but dinner choices are usually limted to 2, and you need to make a reservation at least an hour ahead of time- places to eat in the area are limted Monday- Thursday, so keep that in mind.The road noise gets to you - they are right next to route 3, a busy route.We couldn't use the pool, because it was dirty, and looked like it needed some chemicals added to it. We stayed 5 nights, and had had enough- so we left and didn't get a refund for the remaining nights. Next time I book a place that I don't know about, I will only do a few nights, and stay longer if I like it- lesson learned. 
