<Author>A TripAdvisor Member
<Content>Would not recommend! My husband, 2 small children (3 and 5 year old), and my parents stayed at Caribe Playa in April 2005 for 4 nights. I would not recommend this place to anyone, but especially to people with children. The hotel is very far from the airport (about 3 hours), the road to get there is dangerous and poorly marked, and the hotel is hard to find. It is located right next to the busy road with no land in between. There is nothing to dampen the noise from cars and trucks going by. It is very isolated. There are no restaurants nearby. The nearest and only supermarket is 30 minutes away by car. The hotel restaurant is overpriced and has nothing on the menu for children. There are only 2 menu options for dinner, and the whole time we were there we didn't find it inspiring. You have to let them know whether you will be eating dinner there well in advance, or you are out of luck. Although the hotel is right on the beach, the property is extremely narrow and the beach is rocky and dangerous. You are allowed to swim in the tiny stretch of the beach as there deadly undercurrents right next to the swimming area. The rooms are very outdated, worse than motel quality. You do get a a refrigerator and a coffee maker in the room. We stocked the fridge with bread, cheese, coffee, and fruit from the supermarket and considered ourselves lucky not to have to use the hotel restaurant. I would never again stay in a place that is so isolated from everything else. There are many more places in Puerto Rico with better property and location. 
