<Content>nice place We stayed 5 nights. Beautiful views. Room small but clean. For part of the stay we were 1 group of 3 so we had the place pretty much to ourselvess. The grounds were perfect and very well kept. Very peaceful. Didn't like having to have a reservation to eat in their outdoor place but there was a nice place to eat up the road where they had fresh everything. You need a car to get around, this is the real Puerto Rico mostly locals. Didn't see too many tourists. It's not a grand place but a cute little hideaway with lots of privacy. It was so relaxing I didn't want to go home. 
