<Author>stephen_phillips
<Content>Not Bad Ive Stayed in Much Worse! I was very enchanted by the location of this inn. It is on a little bay of about 1/4mile in length. The hotel sits right on the beach. Its not a beach for walking or swimming. There has been some erosion from hurricanes. Although its a great beach to sit by and read and sunbathe or have a drink! The surroundings of CP are superb.The inn suffers from the cheapness of the management. We paid 147.00 during Xmas for a room which was a great price. But we only got coffee for one night and had to buy packets @ 1.50 for the rest of our stay. Why don't they just raise the price of the room and include the coffee?? There were several small instances of penny pinching like this that got on our nerves.Be forwarned that the restaurants near the hotel are open on the whims of their owners. Therefore the only reliable place to eat dinner is at Caribe Playa and you MUST have a reservation. We were denied food one night because we came in without one. We went to bed without dinner that night....This is a very rugged place. I felt like I was on Dominica and not PR. The pool was beautiful and it was not dirty. The rooms were clean but they were very 3rd world. There had been some hurricane damage that was repaired but noticeable. Its hard running a small hotel down there. This area of PR is very interesting. I wouldn't mind having a house there. This is the only hotel of any quality on the beach in that area. Its not that bad. Id probably stay there again. 
